but I must admit

205
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:44,610
that he is a genius.

206
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:50,100
If we could obtain

207
00:14:50,180 --> 00:14:52,600
Wang Yi Xin's experimental materials,

208
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:55,030
do you have confidence in fixing it?

209
00:14:58,200 --> 00:14:59,870
I'm sure I can fix the machine

210
00:15:00,110 --> 00:15:02,180
if you could obtain the materials.

211
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:06,960
Xiao Dong,

212
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:08,370
my central computer

213
00:15:08,450 --> 00:15:09,550
keeps breaking down.

214
00:15:09,710 --> 00:15:10,880
It affects my productivity.

215
00:15:11,140 --> 00:15:12,310
Aren't you a computer genius?

216
00:15:12,390 --> 00:15:13,220
Check it for me.

217
00:15:13,770 --> 00:15:14,390
Sure.

218
00:15:14,480 --> 00:15:15,090
This way.

219
00:15:16,490 --> 00:15:17,300
Gao Liang!

220
00:15:17,630 --> 00:15:18,360
Gao Liang!

221
00:15:18,680 --> 00:15:19,900
Take Xiao Dong to check on the computer.

222
00:15:20,050 --> 00:15:20,700
Okay.

223
00:15:25,560 --> 00:15:27,430
Professor, is there something
you want to tell me?

224
00:15:32,190 --> 00:15:32,980
Chu Xia,

225
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:35,990
I wonder if you've thought about this.

226
00:15:36,980 --> 00:15:37,870
If

227
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:40,420
you successfully return to ten years ago,

228
00:15:41,510 --> 00:15:43,200
you might need to face

229
00:15:43,750 --> 00:15:44,910
Wei Xuan He

230
00:15:45,030 --> 00:15:46,400
on the night

231
00:15:46,980 --> 00:15:48,500
of November 18th.

232
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:50,080
And

233
00:15:50,630 --> 00:15:52,420
the gravitational wave ten years ago

234
00:15:52,510 --> 00:15:54,710
will once again send you to ten years later.

235
00:15:55,630 --> 00:15:56,870
You'll once again meet Xiao Dong,

236
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:58,300
fall in love with him

237
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:00,870
and the gravitational wave ten years later

238
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:02,390
will still disappear.

239
00:16:03,550 --> 00:16:04,550
And...

240
00:16:05,010 --> 00:16:06,590
I'll return to the past again

241
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:08,320
and go through November 18th.

242
00:16:10,960 --> 00:16:11,790
It's an infinite loop.

243
00:16:12,440 --> 00:16:13,630
Just like

244
00:16:13,750 --> 00:16:16,720
the path integral theory
proposed by Feynman, the physicist.

245
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:18,580
The time particles

246
00:16:18,870 --> 00:16:21,120
will be cyclical in the closed-loop

247
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:23,200
of time and space.

248
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:24,540
It will never end.

249
00:16:29,270 --> 00:16:30,960
You can intuitively understand it

250
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:35,550
as the Mobius strip.

251
00:16:42,120 --> 00:16:43,230
Meaning that

252
00:16:44,030 --> 00:16:45,720
I could never stop Wei Xuan He no matter

253
00:16:46,260 --> 00:16:48,060
how many times I return to the past.

254
00:16:49,390 --> 00:16:51,460
Because the history can never be changed.

255
00:16:54,550 --> 00:16:55,920
Xiao Dong will still have to experience

256
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:57,150
the pain of his dad's death

257
00:16:58,240 --> 00:16:59,960
and his painful personal growth.

258
00:17:02,750 --> 00:17:04,000
And there's nothing I can do

259
00:17:04,310 --> 00:17:05,270
except staying with him.

260
00:17:05,790 --> 00:17:06,960
But your appearance

261
00:17:08,109 --> 00:17:09,470
has brought sunshine

262
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:10,960
into Xiao Dong's life.

263
00:17:11,720 --> 00:17:13,190
Xiao Dong has the courage

264
00:17:13,680 --> 00:17:14,420
to face everything

265
00:17:14,510 --> 00:17:15,640
because of your love and accompany.

266
00:17:18,590 --> 00:17:20,110
As we could encounter and fall in love

267
00:17:20,670 --> 00:17:21,670
countless times,

268
00:17:22,590 --> 00:17:24,200
I think it's worthwhile even if we experience

269
00:17:25,270 --> 00:17:26,550
the anomalies of the universe.

270
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:28,550
But I think

271
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:32,160
there might be another possibility.

272
00:17:33,440 --> 00:17:36,070
Do you know about
the "many-worlds interpretation"?

273
00:17:36,550 --> 00:17:37,680
Many-worlds interpretation

274
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:39,590
was mentioned in Everett's thesis

275
00:17:39,680 --> 00:17:41,160
in the year 1957.

276
00:17:41,510 --> 00:17:43,440
It is also known as the parallel world.

277
00:17:44,450 --> 00:17:45,380
Parallel world?

278
00:17:45,460 --> 00:17:46,160
Yes.

279
00:17:46,680 --> 00:17:47,960
If you return

280
00:17:48,330 --> 00:17:50,310
to November 18th of ten years ago,

281
00:17:50,640 --> 00:17:52,960
you only get back to that moment

282
00:17:53,110 --> 00:17:55,350
but it might not
be that original world of yours.

283
00:17:55,750 --> 00:17:57,830
Maybe it is another parallel world.

284
00:17:58,510 --> 00:17:59,390
If that happens,

285
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:01,660
you'll have different choices.

286
00:18:01,920 --> 00:18:03,490
But every choice you make

287
00:18:03,680 --> 00:18:05,220
will lead to different results.

288
00:18:05,720 --> 00:18:06,590
But Chu Xia,

289
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:08,880
you have to remember this.

290
00:18:10,250 --> 00:18:11,810
Eventually, you'll have to face

291
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:14,550
the destined decision.

292
